  • Class
    Description
    DirectoryInterface
    The DirectoryInterface defines methods for basic directory operations: creating and removing directories.
    Facade
    The Facade class provides a simplified interface for creating and destroying files and directories.
    FileInterface
    The FileInterface defines methods for basic file operations: opening, closing, and deleting files or directories.
    Main
    The Main class is the entry point of the application.
    SubClassDirectory
    The SubClassDirectory class implements the DirectoryInterface and provides specific implementations for creating and removing directories.
    SubClassFile
    The SubClassFile class implements the FileInterface and provides specific implementations for opening, closing, and deleting files.
